	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65032085"><p>Amps, volts, or ohms are still useful here, in order to describe the optimal load. For a completely overexaggerated example, if the battery has an internal resistance of 1 teraohm, it means that, for practical output voltages, it acts as a constant current source of 0.026 microamps, no matter the voltage, and the majority of energy is wasted. To get the claimed 170 microwatts, you would need to allow the output terminals to charge to 13 KV (which would then reduce the output current by half), something comp<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65032085">

