	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65032821">Ok, this is a betavoltaic device - like the Betacel, developed in the 1960ies to power artificial cardiac pacemakers.
<p>
The novel idea hear is the usage of C14 in a diamond structure. C14 is a beta radiator, and diamond is a semiconductor. Instead of a photon causing the emission of a beta particle a.k.a. an electron, like in a solar cell, you use the C14 -&gt; N14 decay.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65032821">

