		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65032037"><p>Carbon has four bonds, nitrogen three. As the carbon 14 decays to nitrogen the diamond will fall apart. After one half-life the average composition will be cyanide.</p><p>Diluting the C14 will extend the life of the crystal structure at the cost of increasing the weight of the power unit.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65032037">
