	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65032081"><p>These things produce less power than the average termite fart.  They have extremely limited applications, such as bios batteries and low power clocks.  I recall seeing one discussing "self-recharging AA batteries", which is fine if you are okay with your AA taking 15 years to recharge.  They're absolutely worthless to the average consumer.</p><p>Go to YouTube and search for "debunk nuclear battery" for several educational videos from well-know and respected presenters.  I especially liked EEVblog's video on the subject.</p></div>
