	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65032245">According to the summary, a standard alkaline AA battery has an energy-storage rating of 700 joules per gram and weighs 20 grams. So that's a total energy storage of 700 * 20 = 14,000 joules. At 15 joules per day, the diamond battery can produce that same amount of energy in 14,000 / 15 = 933.33 days. So it takes about 2.5 years to produce the power contained in one AA battery.

How much trouble is it to replace a AA battery in a low-draw device every 2.5 years? Even if it was fairly cheap, this would have</div>
