		<div id="comment_body_65032583"><p>The part I might screw up:</p><p>An AA battery gives you 700j/g.  You have 20g of AA, so 14000j.  Then you're going to divide that number by 15j, the amount of energy the diamond battery can produce per gram daily. You get ~933.  So for every "AA battery-day" you need 933x the mass in diamond batteries to get the equivalent power, except you keep getting that same power day after day after day.</p><p>Now comes the fun bit I'll almost certainly screw up.</p><p>The Voyager probes have three RTGs each, with an initial power output<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
